{
  "text": "(b) Immobilized neurexin 1\u2423 quantitatively removed \u2423-dystroglycan from brain homogenates, indicating complete binding (Fig. 3) . (c) Neurexins are coimmunoprecipitated with \u2423-and \u2424-dystroglycans from brain homogenates (Fig.  4) . (d) The neurexin 1\u2423 overlay assay revealed specific binding of neurexin 1\u2423 to \u2423-dystroglycan in ES cells (Fig. 5 A) and in mouse tissues (Fig. 6 A) . (e) A soluble recombinant neurexin 1\u2423 Ig fusion protein specifically bound to the surface of cells expressing dystroglycan but not to cells lacking dystroglycan (Fig. 5 B) . (f) Finally, the excitatory neurotoxin \u2423-latrotoxin, which is a natural ligand for neurexins [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , competes with dystroglycan for binding to neurexins (Fig. 9) .",
